    <div>
        <h1> BUY COINS </h1>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h3 class="headings"> Post Decimal Australian Currency (after 1966) </h3> 
        <section>
            <p> On the 14th of Feburary 1966, the Australian dollar was introduced to replace the Australian Pound. The old Australian Pound was converted into two Australian Dollars. The denominations of the Dollar are 5 cents, 10 cents, 20 cents, 50 cents, 1 dollar and 2 dollars. Please click the photo to see our current inventory!</p>
        </section>
        <section class ="photo">
            <%= link_to (image_tag "postdecimalcurrency.jpg", alt: "Pictures of Australian 5 cent, 10 cent, 20 cent, 50 cent, 1 dollar and 2 dollar coins"), postdecimal_path %>
        </section>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h3 class="headings"> Pre Decimal Australian Currency (1901-1966) </h3>
        <section>
            <p> The Australian Pound, was the currency of Australia following the Federation of Australia in 1901. The coins of the Australian pound were; Half Penny, Penny, Threepence, Sixpence, Shilling, Florin and Crown. Please click the photo to see our current inventory! 
        </section>
        <section class ="photo">
            <%= link_to (image_tag "imageofpredecimalcoins.jpg", alt: "Pictures of Australian half-penny, penny, 3 pence, 6 pence, shilling, florin, and crown"), predecimal_path  %>
        </section>
    </div>
    <div>
        <%= render "shared/footer" %>
    </div>
